Here are my 2 cents.
=C2=A0
Jnana yoga emphasizes on philosophiza=
tion and wisdom. Karma yoga emphasizes on work and detachment. Raja yoga em=
phasizes on self-control and self-mastery. Bhakti yoga emphasizes on devoti=
on and surrender to Supreme. One can pick whatever is natural to one and tr=
y to develop that quality. However, wisdom, detached action, self-control a=
nd surrender to the Supreme are not mutually exclusive. As one of these qua=
lities develops nicely in one, others will automatically develop too! Final=
ly, a realized person (i.e. one in "Yoga" or oneness) will have all these q=
ualities fully blossomed.
=C2=A0
Forget about horoscope, navamsa, vimsamsa,=
 nakshatramsa etc. Irrespective of that, I strongly recommend against Raja =
yoga for 99% of humanity. Even Ramakrishna advised
 against it. Controlling=
 body and mind and forcing the psychic life force to purify and ascend requ=
ires strict yama and niyama and clean nadis. In this age of polluted air, w=
ater and food, nadis accumulate great amounts of obstructions and Raja yoga=
 can be dangerous. This is not just my view, but what Ramakrishna explicitl=
y taught in "Gospel of Ramakrishna" (one of the greatest spiritual texts IM=
HO). He discouraged several of his sishyas from pursuing Raja Yoga. He taug=
ht it to Vivekananda, but did not encourage even him to practice it.
=C2=A0=

Jnana yoga is brilliant, but there is a distinct danger of falling into th=
e delusional trap of pseudo-wisdom. People of this age are not sincere/hone=
st/smart enough for it. It is easy to delude that "all is Brahman. I am Bra=
hman. Whatever I do, it's ok - it doesn't matter. It's all a delusion anywa=
y" without fully overcoming all innate conditioning that reinforces duality=
 in consciousness every instant. Kind
 of like declaring wisely in a movie =
that "it's just a movie and not reality", but flinching in every scary scen=
e, crying in every sad scene etc. Without absolute honesty, sincerely and e=
arnestness, jnana yoga can be problematic too. A long path of constant cont=
emplation and self-correction can be reduced to a quick delusional jump to =
the end.
=C2=A0
IMHo, for most people in this age, Bhakti yoga and Karma yo=
ga are the most suitable and safest.
=C2=A0
